metadata.name: Pebbles #49
metadata.description:
Generative series in six different ranges of 30 colors each that are combined with 150 colors forming a wall. "The Pebbles" series pays tribute to these first ancestral wall constructions in dry stone without concrete to hold them together. It is an ancient technique that dates back to the Stone Age.

This series of generatives NFTs is born from the drawings presented in Milan at the Galería Patricia Armocida. They are composed of stone blocks in 6 series of 50 originals in which 30 colors per range are combined with 150 secondary range colors in infinite shapes.

http://www.nuriamora.com/serie-piedras/

The first Range is Blue.


Coded in P5js.

Source code based on Roni Kaufman previous work and used under a collaborative agreement.

metadata.name: Plant remains #18
metadata.description:
Black and white photography, from film to digital to constrained and dithered greys palette 2500x2500 pixels. 

Layered tonalities from six film scans piling randomly.

Pics made in the south of France : the mountains above Grasse for the thistles and around the lake of St Cassien when it was very low, showing the old stumps usually hidden under the water.

Those stumps are remains of the nature before the lake was created in the 60's.
Sometimes when the lake is very low i take some time to shoot what's hidden under the surface.

The thistles are all dead in the pics (autumn), in some you can see the seeds preparing a new start for the following season.

Rare types of colors can show up in the last translucent layer to honor old analog photography : Cyanotype (1/5), Vandyke (1/10), Virage (1/10)

Some results can be strange but that's the point of random exploration. Feel free to try variations before minting ;-)

Click on the opened image to generate a download icon.

If you want to print the image please upscale without interpolation to preserve the dithering.

By Palancus (@Palancus)

Previous collectors have a reserved mint for a few days after release.

Big thanks to @PureSpider for his useful template.

metadata.name: anaglyphic gazing portrait #15
metadata.description:
Each mint generates a unique interactive anaglyphic portrait. 
The portrait's gaze follows the cursor. Hover the portrait to activate.

Each mint has a 5% chance of becoming a rare MEGAGLYPH. 
Each mint has a very low chance of becoming a null (each half-face is a circle).

MEGAGLYPHs have a red border. The bottom-left [anaglyph] stamp is replaced with a [megaglyph] stamp.

metadata.name: Prospettive Astratte - Floating structures #18
metadata.description:
Perspective and abstraction, generates 3D a structure, a grid of floating objects projected in perspective, in some cases a close up detail. Sometime close to a regular pattern, sometime more chaotic like any urban development. 
Inside complex generated textures, based on a colored palette tanke from a Leonardo Da Vinci and Botticelli painting

By either MOUSE CLICKING over the canvas or touching it, color palette will redistribute over the *same* token shape, as well transparency will be affected. This could give the effect of a changing shape, while instead are hidden shapes "re-emerging" from transparency, while other may disappear.
